Package org.hl7.xml.parser

Interface Summary
DynamicContentHandler A SAX ContentHandler that keeps a reference to the XMLReader that it is registered with.
DynamicContentHandler.ResultReceiver A content handler result receiver is an object that expects a notification once the content handler is done.
Extensible An interface implemented by objects that are extensible with arbitrary XML node-sets.
 

Class Summary
DataTypeContentHandler A DynamicContentHandler used for data types.
DynamicContentHandlerBase An abstract base class that make implementation of DynamicContentHandlers easier.
IgnoreContentHandler A dynamic content handler that lets us simply ignore whatever else we find.
MessageContentHandler A simple thing that bootstraps the XML parsing process.
MessageElementContentHandler An XML SAX content handler for parsing generic HL7 message elements that stem from RIM class clones.
SimpleTypeContentHandler A simple type content handler is a dynamic content handler that by default ignores any content nodes (elements or text) and only considers attributes unless an known result is known before passing xml element.
StandaloneDataTypeContentHandler A simple thing that bootstraps the XML parsing process for standalone data type value.
TreeContentHandler A DynamicContentHandler used to generate small (mini-DOM) trees that can be used in two ways: - as an intermediary representation for a value constructor to get the parameters.
TreeContentHandler.Attribute  
TreeContentHandler.Element  
TreeContentHandler.NamedNode  
TreeContentHandler.Node A super simple DOM that simply collects SAX elements, attributes and text nodes.
TreeContentHandler.Text
